tries to find some kind of nefarious motives in everything. Management is quite
self-dealing too, but not necessarily totally against shareholders, since they
are large shareholders themselves. That's what makes some plays quite cheap.
Management buyout arbitrage premiums have shrunk to unplayable levels though,
since most of them went through.
